org.fdsn.xml.station._1

Class RootType

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.fdsn.xml.station._1.RootType

  • public class RootType
extends java.lang.Object
    Top-level type for Station XML. Required fields are Source (network ID of the institution sending the message), Created (creation time of the document) and one or more Network containers.

    Java class for RootType complex type.

    The following schema fragment specifies the expected content contained within this class. 

     <complexType name="RootType">
   <complexContent>
     <restriction base="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}anyType">
       <sequence>
         <element name="Source" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string"/>
         <element name="Sender" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="Module" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="ModuleURI" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}anyURI" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="Created" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}dateTime"/>
         <element name="Network" type="{http://www.fdsn.org/xml/station/1}NetworkType" maxOccurs="unbounded"/>
         <any/>
       </sequence>
       <attribute name="schemaVersion" use="required" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}decimal" />
     </restriction>
   </complexContent>
 </complexType>
